Okay, the X10s are online.
Hang on, hang on, do you not realise what we just did.
No, no, no, you don’t get it, um, Howard, enable public access.
No, hang on, hang on. (The lamp goes off and on again.) See!
Wireless webcams, wave hello.
Who’s running the red Corvette?
Sheldon, why is this letter in the trash?
It’s from the Institute for Experimental Physics. They want us to present our paper on the properties of super solids at the topical conference on Bowes-Einstein condensates.
Okay… if I may drill down to the bedrock of my question, why did you throw it out.
Forget the parties.
Are there any other honours I’ve gotten that I don’t know about? Did UPS drop off a Nobel Prize with my name on it?
Shut up, Howard. Sheldon, we have to do this.
Okay, let me put it this way, I’m doing it.
Oh, come on. The only reason you’re the lead author is because we went alphabetically.
Excuse me, I designed the experiment that proved the hypothesis.
So the entire scientific community is just supposed to take your word?
Alright, I don’t care what you say, I’m going to the conference and I’m presenting our findings.
You forbid it?
Oh, you admit that it’s our work.
Ah!

Not only is he still not talking to me, but there’s this thing he does where he stares at you and tries to get your brain to explode. You know, like in the classic sci-fi movie Scanners? (Put’s fingers to head) You know, bzzz-pchew! Never mind. How about this one. It says, “I know my physics, but I’m still a fun guy!”
They don’t, that’s why I saved this one.
Is this all stuff you want me to try on?
Oh.
Oh, that’s the bottled city of Kandor.
You see, Kandor was the capital city of the planet Krypton, it was miniaturised by Brainiac before Krypton exploded and then rescued by Superman.
It’s a lot cooler when girls aren’t looking at it.
Great, be right back.
Here?
No, I’m not shy.
I know you won’t look, why would you look, there’s nothing to see, well, not nothing….
Putting them on.
No. No. Scientists do not compromise. Our minds are trained to synthesise facts and come to inarguable conclusions. Not to mention, Sheldon is batcrap crazy.
Oh, careful. That’s my original series Battlestar Galactica flight suit.
Because it’s not a costume, it’s a flight suit.
Uh-huh, it goes with my corduroy suit.
Ah. Technically yes, but, if you’ll notice, it’s reversible. So it works as two.
Yeah. Everything since the eighth grade.
My last growth spurt.
Great.
What… (Sheldon goes into apartment and slams the door).
Okay, I’m leaving for the conference.
Sheldon I didn’t mean it like that.
I don’t know, I wasn’t choosing my…
No, no not at all. A little bit.
Okay, I’m going to ask you one more time, we did the work together, lets present the paper together.
Let’s go.
You’re right, this side does look better.
You’re kidding.
All? In particle physics, twenty five is Woodstock.
I wasn’t expecting such a crowd, I’m a little nervous.

A joke. Okay. How about this, um, okay, uh there’s this farmer, and he has these chickens, but they won’t lay any eggs. So, he calls a physicist to help. The physicist then does some calculations, and he says, um, I have a solution, but it only works with spherical chickens in a vacuum. (Raj and Howard laugh.) Right?
It’s a classic, right?

So, in conclusion, the data show that at temperatures approaching absolute zero, the moment of inertia changes, and the solid becomes a super-solid, which clearly appears to be a previously unknown state of matter. (Applause) Thank you. (Penny is asleep on Howard’s shoulder. Howard is taking a photograph with his camera phone.) Are there any questions?
Any other questions?
I didn’t skip it, it’s just an anecdote. It’s not science.
You are not Isaac Newton.
You cannot possibly be that arrogant.
Look, if you weren’t happy with my presentation then maybe you should have given it with me.
Really, so why did you come?
I didn’t screw it up.

I’ve had enough of your condescension. Maybe I didn’t go to college when I was eleven like you, maybe I got my doctorate at 24 instead of 16, but you are not the only person who is smarter than everyone else in this room. No offense. And I am clearly not the only person who is tormented by insecurity and has an ego in need of constant validation.
Yes. (To audience) My name is Dr Leonard Hofstadter, and I could never please my parents so I need to get all my self-esteem from strangers like you. But he’s worse.
You cannot blow up my head with your mind.
You were trying to blow up my head.
It wasn’t, it was not, you are a nutcase.
Stop, stop it, quit it. (The start to fight.)
You’re lucky I didn’t run you over.
You’re right, I’m the problem, I’m the one that needs help.
Excuse me. Is there anything you’d like to apologise for?
What?
Oh jeez. Is this suit really look that bad?
See, the liquid metal Terminators were created in the future by Skynet, and Skynet was developed by Miles Dyson, but that future no longer exists, due to Dyson’s death in Terminator 2.
Skynet is kinky? I don’t know.
Alright, oh wait, they use it to in…
What the hell is that?
What? Oh we just had to… mail some letters and (seeing Sheldon has large bag in hand and bin is nearby) throw away some chicken. (Sheldon very reluctantly does.)
Oh, I give up.
Believe it or not, personal growth. What happened?
No you don’t. No he doesn’t.
Oh, congratulations, what a lucky break.
No you don’t. He doesn’t.
Because…. uh, Friday, we are attending a symposium on molecular positronium.
No, it’s this Friday, at eight.
See you. (Penny exits singing)
Yes, I did.
So?
Sheldon, are you worried about your safety.
That’s very true.
What?
It’s two o’clock in the morning
I highly doubt that. Go away. (Long pause). Are you still out there?
Sheldon, what is it?
What was I supposed to say.
That would have hurt her feelings.
Yes.
And what would I have said afterwards?
I couldn’t say that, I would have to say, you were terrific and I can’t wait to hear you sing again.
It’s the social protocol, it’s what you do when you have a friend who’s proud of something they really suck at.
Well now you are.
Yes.
Oooaw. This would be so much easier if I were a violent sociopath. (Opening door) What?
How?
You told her I lied, why would you tell her I lied?
I’m sorry, I’m not seeing the help.
Oh, I’m getting a bad feeling.
Your cousin Leopold?
What’s important?
Do you have a cousin Leopold.
I don’t get it, I already told her a lie, why replace it with a different lie?
Un-unravelable?
Okay, why would I go to a drug intervention for your cousing.
We’re going to Long Beach?
Oh, come on!
So he goes back into rehab?
You still told her I lied.
I don’t know. How am I supposed to remember all of this.
So she’s expecting me to lie about going to a symposium in Pasadena, when in actuality we’re pretending to go to a drug intervention in Long Beach?
Oh, well, thankyou.
I don’t know what to say.
Oh, okay, alright, good.
Howard, I’m sorry… we’re… we’re
I don’t know what to say.
Howard, listen…
Well… I don’t know what to say.
Oh, another hug, thank you.
Thanks Penny.
No, we’re not going to Long Beach.
Because Sheldon doesn’t have a drug addicted cousin Leopold.
Wait, are we really going to Long Beach?
Let it go, Sheldon, the murderer was the first mate whether it makes sense to you or not.
What are you talking about, it’s fine, she bought it, it’s over.
Why not?
There is no Leo, how can you say that?
I’ve got a solution.
Get out.
Who are you?
Oh, God! Sheldon does not have a cousin Leo.
Sheldon?
Yeah, I got it, Sheldon, why?
Oh…!
Well, that’s Leo. Hey, um, why don’t you tell me about your showcase last night?
There were only two people there?
As you can see, detoxing can get pretty ugly, let’s give them some privacy.
Sounds good.
Gee, why wouldn’t I?
Yeah! Funny how things work out.
How long is he going to stay here.

dialogue: I mix pancake batter in this!

dialogue: Yes.

dialogue: Yes.

dialogue: Oh, hi Penny!

dialogue: Uh, yeah, I’d be… I’d be happy to Penny. (Holds phone up, Howard makes warning siren noises) Oh my God there’s a breech in the radiation unit (Raj joins in) The whole city is in jeopardy, oh my God, Professor Googenfeil is melting, gotta go, bye! (To Howard and Raj) I feel really guilty.

dialogue: Oh dammit, my glasses. Okay, I’m blind here guys, can you help me find them?

episode_name: Series 01 Episode 11 – The Pancake Batter Anomaly
dialogue: Oh great.

dialogue: Yeah, at home.

dialogue: You want me to get eye surgery?

dialogue: What do you see, what do you see.

episode_name: Series 01 Episode 11 – The Pancake Batter Anomaly
dialogue: Okay, he must be in his bedroom. My spare glasses are in my bedroom, on my dresser, next to my Bat-signal.

dialogue: Raj?

episode_name: Series 01 Episode 11 – The Pancake Batter Anomaly
dialogue: Well I can’t do it, I can’t see anything.

dialogue: Fine.

dialogue: Won’t my footsteps set it off?

dialogue: What?

dialogue: Then just say go straight.

episode_name: Series 01 Episode 11 – The Pancake Batter Anomaly
dialogue: Alright (Bangs head on a trunk.) I just hit my head.

dialogue: It wasn’t on?

dialogue: Then why did I have to crawl?

episode_name: Series 01 Episode 11 – The Pancake Batter Anomaly
dialogue: Okay, it’s on.

episode_name: Series 01 Episode 11 – The Pancake Batter Anomaly
dialogue: I know.

episode_name: Series 01 Episode 11 – The Pancake Batter Anomaly
dialogue: Hi!

episode_name: Series 01 Episode 11 – The Pancake Batter Anomaly
dialogue: Well, I had to, you see what he’s like.

episode_name: Series 01 Episode 11 – The Pancake Batter Anomaly
dialogue: No!

dialogue: W-wait!

dialogue: Wait! Penny! Take me with you! (Runs after her and bumps into pillar. Falls semi-conscious to the floor.  Sheldon appears in his comforter.)

dialogue: I don’t think Penny’s ever coming here again.

dialogue: Yeah, so?

dialogue: If I stand, I’ll vomit.
Lay it on me.
How about that.
Would the new Sheldon be in any way an improvement on the old Sheldon?
That is a problem.
Graduate work, very impressive.
Advantage Kim.
Yes sir.
So, Dennis, how long have you been in America.
No kidding, you speak English really well.
What are you talking about?
Come on, Sheldon, we’ve hardly shown him anything.
Huh, yeah?
Come on, Dennis, I’ll show you the rec centre, they’ve got nautilus equipment.
Not heavy ones.
Come on, Dennis, I’ll show you the radiation lab.
It’s like looking into an obnoxious little mirror, isn’t it?
Something you’d like to share? A tale of woe perhaps.
Just eat, Sheldon, you’ll feel better.
You can’t let this kid get to you. You always knew that someday someone would come along who was younger and smarter.
Well, what are you going to do, Sheldon, give up?
Hey.
Great.
Great.
Great.
Okay, well, right now I’m designing an experiment to study the soft component of cosmic radiation at sea-level, but I really don’t need any help.
Yes.
It would blow up.
Pretty sure.

Okay, Sheldon, I understand that you’re going through a bit of a career crisis, you’re searching for some other area where you can feel valuable and productive but I need to tell you something and I want you to listen carefully.
Go away.
If he were, I wouldn’t be.
Is that even possible?
Like what? He’ll never be able to cope with the fact that some fifteen year-old kid is smarter and more accomplished than he is.
Hang on, are we talking about murdering Dennis Kim? I’m not saying no.
That won’t happen, he’s not interested in anything but physics.
What?
Howard, he’s fifteen.
Howard, that’s racist, any fifteen year-old girl will do the trick. (Penny slams door.)
It’s take your daughter to work day.
Okay, so we now have a socially awkward genius in a room full of attractive age-appropriate women.
Does anyone else see the flaw in this plan?
Like what? We can’t get fifteen year-old girls drunk.
No, we can’t.
Okay, we cannot leave this to chance, lets pick a girl, and figure out how to get her together with Dennis.

Sure. If he wants to spend a couple of years doing her homework while she drinks herself into a stupor with non-fat White Russians, while you’re the one holding her head out of the toilet while she’s puking and telling you she wishes more guys were like you, and they she gets into Cornell because you wrote her essay for her, and you drive up to visit her one weekend and she acts like she doesn’t even know you.
I think that’s our girl. One of us should go talk to her.
I can’t just go up and talk to her. Howard, you talk to her.
Well, we’re not in India.
Okay, that was uncalled for.
The kid got a girl.
Yeah, mission accomplished.
Well, why do we go home alone every night, we’re still smart.
I don’t know if the ticket was so much for the launch as it was for you telling the policewoman “you have to frisk me, I have a rocket in my pants.”
Yeah, we really ruined his life.

episode_name: Series 01 Episode 13 – The Bat Jar Conjecture
dialogue: What are you doing?

episode_name: Series 01 Episode 13 – The Bat Jar Conjecture
dialogue: Bring it on.

episode_name: Series 01 Episode 13 – The Bat Jar Conjecture
dialogue: How do you know these things?

episode_name: Series 01 Episode 13 – The Bat Jar Conjecture
dialogue: Wait, I don’t think it’s Shatner.
I don’t believe it.
Some guy is auctioning off a miniature time machine prop from the original film and no-one is bidding on it.
No, a time machine from Sophie’s Choice.
Uh-huh.
Yeah. And that’s my bid.
It was a spur of the moment thing, I figured it would go for thousands and I just wanted to be a part of it.
Not to blow on a miniature time machine.
Come on, snipers.
Where are your snipers?
Snipe.
Snipe.
Snipe!
SNIPE!
Aaaa-aw!
Yeah, I know, I still can’t afford it.
I just assumed. Who sells a full sized time machine for $800?
How are we going to get it upstairs?
Yes but the elevator’s been broken for two years.
Come on, guys, push.
Oh, just, you know, moving… something upstairs.
It’s… you know, time machine.
Uh, just give us a few minutes.
Hey, if you wait for us to set up the time machine, I can drop you off at work yesterday. Time travel joke, it’s not… never mind.
Let’s just do this. Guys, ready to push?
Yeah. It is by far the coolest thing I have ever owned.
Seconded.
That sounds fair.

Sheldon, you can’t be selfish, we all paid for it, so it belongs to all of us. Now out of the way so I can sit in my time machine. (Sits and turns it on. The three lights on the front illuminate. All let out an “oh”.) Okay, I am setting the dials for March 10th, 1876.
So, when it’s your turn you can.

Okay, I am setting the dials for January 10th, 2328. Here we go into the future. (Pulls lever, the disk begins to spin. The other guys all run around the flat as if moving in fast motion.) That was fun.
Are you okay?
That doesn’t sound too bad.
Sorry.
The lights flash and the dish spins, you wanna try it?
So?
Because I want to go back and keep myself from getting a time machine.
Can I go back and prevent you from explaining that to me?
What if I knocked you unconscious right now?
But it would make the present so much nicer.
What was your first clue?
Yes I’m upset.
Yeah, good for you.
I don’t know. Maybe.
Uh, here’s the thing. Girls like Penny never end up with guys who own time machines.
Thanks for pointing it out.
Those are movies.
Come on, guys, push.
Oh, just, you know, moving a… time machine.
No problem. (Removes glasses, pulls down out of order tape from lift doors, and forces them open.) Hang on. (Takes Penny in his arms as he holds onto the lift cable.)
Some things are more important than toys. (She puts her arms around his neck as he dangles from the cable.)
Don’t worry baby, I’ve got you.
I’m packing up all my collectibles and taking them down to the comic book store to sell.
It’s not about money.
Terrific, does anyone want to buy my share of the time machine?
Because I don’t want it any more.
Just… personal reasons.
Look, do you want to buy me out or not?
I paid two hundred dollars for my share.
No, no more toys or action figures or props or replicas or costumes or robots or Darth Vader voice changers, I’m getting rid of all of it.
Not for long.
It’s not a bidding war, I’m selling it all to Larry down at the comic book store.
He offered me a fair price for the whole collection.
Forget it guys, if I sell to one of you, the other two are going to be really mad at me.
Sorry Raj, my mind is made up.
Sheldon, get out of my way.

Okay. I did not want to do this but, I have here the rare mint condition production error Star Trek: The Next Generation Geordi LaForge, without his visor in the original packaging. If you do not get out of my way, I will open it.
No, I needed to hear it.
Still, I think it’s time for me to get rid of this stuff and… you know… move on with my life.
Yeah.
Thanks. Hey, do you want to, I don’t know, later…
Sheldon, are you okay?
It is a little big for the living room, isn’t it?
I’m glad you agree. I hired some guys to help us move it, come on in fellas. (A pair of Morlocks come through the door.)
On the other hand, some physicists are concerned that if the super collider actually works, it will create a black hole and swallow up the Earth ending life as we know it.
I don’t know, Raj. Maybe the comic book store doesn’t have a bulletin board. (Sees crowds in the corridor) What’s going on?
Sheldon’s office? Is she lost?
Maybe she’s his lawyer.
Howard…
Oh, hey buddy.
Sheldon, are you going to introduce us?
You too, swell, also.
So, how do you two know each other.
Excuse me?
So Missy, what brings you all the way from Texas?
If the wedding’s not until tomorrow, why don’t you stay with us tonight?
Look, you’re here, we have plenty of room.
So it’s settled. You’ll stay with us.
Hee-hee, just classic.
Those are not mine.

Yeah, no, I do, I use those… uh… just to polish up my… spear-fishing equipment. I spear fish. When I’m not crossbow hunting, I spear fish. Uh, Penny, this is Sheldon’s twin sister, Missy. Missy, this is our neighbour Penny.
I wasn’t staring!
Oh. Huh, um, maybe, if you like women who are tall… and perfect.
I brought snacks.
Onion dip, it’s onion dip.
We don’t entertain much.
Bye Missy, see you.
Uh, yeah, no, uh, bye Penny.
Excuse me, this is my apartment and she’s my roommate’s sister.
How do I have Penny? In what universe do I have Penny?
Hell, no!
Sheldon, can I talk to you in private?
Thank you.
Sheldon, are you aware that your sister is an incredibly attractive woman?
That’s fascinating, but I…
Alright, noted. But my point is that Koothrappali and Wolowitz… they’re hitting on your sister.
That’s great, but I….
Whatever. You have to do something about it.
Because she’s your sister.
Okay, uh…. oh, consider this. With your father gone, it is your responsibility to make sure that Missy chooses a suitable mate.
Uh-huh.
Exactly. And, you owe it to yourself and to posterity to protect the genetic integrity of your sister’s future offspring.
He’s the man of his family, you have to respect his wishes.
Say what?
We all make mistakes, let’s move on.
Sheldon, you are really being unreasonable.
I agree. Sheldon’s sister is hiding at Penny’s because we’ve all been hitting on her at the same time.
Sit down.
If we’re going to fight over Missy, let’s do it the right way. The honourable way.
And he’s down!
Stay down, bitch. Yeah, ha ha, natural selection at work.
Excuse me while I go tell Missy the good news. (Leaves and knocks on Penny’s door.)
Hi Penny, how’s it going. Listen, that guy Mike that you were dating, is that still going on?
Nothing, just catching up. By the way, may I speak to Missy please?
Well, since you’re leaving tomorrow I was wondering if you’d like to go out to dinner with me?
Oh. You have other plans, or…?
Oh. Alright uh… enjoy the rest of your evening.
Oh, it’s called trestling.
Forget about the cake, how did you know that my birthday is Saturday?
Oh, I don’t think so.
I don’t celebrate my birthday.
No, it’s no big deal, it’s just the way I was raised. My parents focussed on celebrating achievements, and being expelled from a birth canal was not considered one of them.
Thank you.

No. But it was okay. I mean, when I was little I’d think maybe my parents would change their mind, and surprise me with a party, like this one birthday I came home from my Cello lesson, and I saw a lot of strange cars parked out front, and when I got to the door I could hear people whispering, and I could smell German chocolate cake, which is my favourite.
Uh, it turns out my grandfather had died.
Oh, it was kind of like a birthday party. I got to see all my cousins and there was cake, so…7
Howard, every Thai restaurant in town knows you can’t eat peanuts. They see me coming they go “ah, no peanut boy!”
Hey.
Fine.
Seen it.
Oh. Pass.
Look, I am in the Halo battle of my life here, there’s this kid in Copenhagen, he has no immune system so all he does is sit in his bubble and play Halo 24/7.
Not if you believe his doctors.
No.

Here you go, Copenhagen boy, how about a taste of Hans Christian Hand Grenade. (Raj enters carrying party supplies. Howard waves him away while in the background Leonard is heard saying “oh, that did not feel good.”) Come on, come on, oh you clever little…. Come on, come on, take that!
What’s the matter?
Oh my God, why did you eat it?
Well if I had a gun there, would you have shot yourself?
Now?
Alright, um, just, uh, let me get my keys.
Really, ‘cos you don’t look like you’re swelling up at all, maybe we should just pick up some benedryl at the drug store and go home.
Why not?
Alright, I’ll be right back.
Excuse me, my friend is having an allergic reaction to peanuts.
Yes he is.
Say what you will about the healthcare system in this country, but when they’re afraid of lawsuits they sure test everything.
You know, before you got all swollen up, I actually thought you were trying to keep me out of the apartment so you could throw me a surprise party.
There is a party, isn’t there.
Howard.
how could I be mad? You actually risked your life because you cared about me.
Alright. Here we go. My first birthday party.
Oh, it’s okay.
Hey Penny, when, uh, when’s your birthday?
Why are you learning Chinese?
If I were you, I’d be more concerned by what they’re passing off as chicken.
Oh, yeah, no, sure, go ahead.
What’s going on?
Penny, are you okay?
Look, I understand that breaking up with someone can be very painful….
Okay, feel better, bye. (Goes back to apartment) She doesn’t want to talk.
It was Penny’s boyfriend’s, they broke up.
You know what, I’m going to go back and try talking to her again.
I’m not going to do that, Howard.
What about “damsel in distress?”
I don’t care. She’s upset, I’m going over there.
I’m her friend, I’m not going to take advantage of her vulnerability.
I said I’m her friend. Not her gay friend.
Wait, did you say wait?
No. No.
Of course not.
I’m sorry, what were the choices again?
Yeah, no, sure.
Actually it’s not all that easy to find.
Okay, well, what exactly did this guy write, not that I need to know the details of your sex life, I just thought…. never mind.
Okay, well, you know, this isn’t that bad. It just paints the picture of a very affectionate woman who’s open to expressing her affection in non traditional locales.
Elevators, parks, movie theatres, out of curiosity, is this subway the transportation system or subway the sandwich shop?
Doesn’t that violate the health code?
Huh. Okay. But my point is that you have absolutely no reason to be embarrassed.
Maybe a little.
No. No, no, that, that would be underreacting. He did break the implied confidentiality of the bedroom and, in your case, the elevator, parks and fast food franchise.
Yes, you should, go ahead, say it.
What is there to explain, it’s all right here, it’s a betrayal.
I’m pretty sure I never said that.
Aw, good for me. Where are you going?
Oh, sure. Huh, maybe I am her gay friend.
Can we please change the subject.
Just roll the dice.
She was mad at him. She was done with him, the relationship was broken beyond repair and I walked over there and I fixed it!
Just eat your tangerine chicken.
What happened?
Yeah, I know, I know that part.
Already, that was quick.
Oh, Penny, I am so sorry.
Oh, well, you know, you did throw an 8 gig iPod… yeah, no, how could he do that.
Yeah, that must get old quick.
What about me?
What about if you went out with me?
Um… yes… I am… asking you out.
I was just going off your comment about the nice guy…
Yes what?
Really?
Yeah. That’s the spirit.
Sheldon, I think I’ve made a mistake.
No, it’s about Penny.
I don’t think I can go out with her tonight.
Other people would say “why not?”
I’m going to talk anyway.
Now that I’m actually about to go out with Penny, I’m not excited, I’m nauseous.
Right.
Sheldon, this date is probably my one chance with Penny, what happens if I blow it.
You’re not helping.
Tell me whether or not to go through with the date.
Wow, that’s brilliant.
Hi.
Thank you. You look very nice.
I made an eight o’clock reservation.
Oh. Okay. But before you say anything, have you ever heard of Schrodinger’s Cat?
Good. (He grabs her and kisses her.)

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: So you see, what you’re eating is not technically yoghurt, because it doesn’t have enough live acidophilus cultures. It’s really just iced milk with carragenin added for thickness.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: It’s also not pink and has no berries.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: What was your question again?

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: Oh, right, no, I’m lactose intolerant.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: So, gas.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: Well, good night. (They kiss. Camera cuts away to a wall mounted security cam above the lift. Leonard spots its movement and shuffles Penny away.)

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: There was a draft.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: Why don’t we just go into your….

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: No, no, I didn’t mean to go into your apartment to… go fast.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: Yeah, okay, sure, no problem, why don’t we just figure out where we’re going, and when we want to get there, and then rate of speed equals distance over time. Solve for R.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: That might work too.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: Goodnight. (He throws the camera a dirty look.)

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: Bite me. Sheldon, how could you just sit there and let them spy on me?

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: What are you talking about, the date went fine.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: Okay, so, she said she wants to slow things down. It’s like saying “I’m really enjoying this meal, I’m going to slow down and savour it.”

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: I’m not the fish.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: Well, we sort of decided to wing it.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: Okay, alright, let’s assume your hypothesis. We went to dinner, we talked, we laughed, we kissed, where could I have possibly gone wrong.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: I didn’t say anything like that.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: Look, everything went fine. I didn’t even have to refer to my impromptu conversation starters. The woman across the hall is into me.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: That’s not a bad sign.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: I’m not there because I’m taking things slow. Which, by the way, compared to you guys approaches warp speed. And take down that camera.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: You could be Batman?

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: Hey.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: Hey, Penny, if you’re not doing anything Friday night I thought maybe we could go and see a movie.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: What about Saturday?

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: Great. So you just let me know when you know. So… (she leaves) Oh God, I am the bad fish! What did I do wrong?

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: No I didn’t.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: What’s going on with you?

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: What’s wrong with your face?

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: What?

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: Good day?

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: What do you mean, you’re moving out? Why?

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: Yeah, there kind of does.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: I’m still confused.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: It’s not you, Howard, he says he’s moving out.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: No.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: No.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: No.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: I didn’t do anything, he’s just gone insane.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: That was fast.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: Where are you gonna live?

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: This could work.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: I’m coming! (Opens the door. Sheldon falls inside, wearing his pyjamas. Howard is outside.)

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: What’s with him?

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: I still don’t know why you left.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: Why not.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: You promised Penny what?

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: What secret. Tell me the secret.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: Not that secret, the other secret.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: Dammit, Sheldon! You said Penny told you a secret, what was the secret.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: I promise.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: So it’s nothing I did? It’s her problem?

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: Penny thinks I’m too smart for her, that’s ridiculous.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: Yeah, hi, listen, I know what’s been bothering you about us, and I have the answer.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: First I want to say that it’s not Sheldon’s fault, he tried very hard to keep your secret, if Howard hadn’t drugged him he would have taken it to his grave.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: Yes, but it’s okay. Now that we know what the problem is, there’s a simple solution. (Hands her a brochure.)

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: A place for fun, a place for knowledge. See, this man here’s playing hacky sack, and this girl’s going to be a paralegal.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: Well, it’s really not that fancy, it’s just a city college.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: That doesn’t matter to me at all.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 01 – The Bad Fish Paradigm
dialogue: Absolutely. (She slams the door in his face.) Okay, this time I know where I went wrong. (Looking up and seeing the camera) Oh bite me!
Please let it go, Sheldon.
You’re nitpicking.
Hi.
So, yeah, good to see you.
It wasn’t awkward. It wasn’t fun. Besides, what’s the big deal, we dated, we stopped dating, and now we’re both moving on.
Can we please just go in, my chain mail is stuck in my underwear.
Relatively modern. Why, what are you wearing?
You went out and bought linen?
Borrowed?
You know what, I’m happy that Penny’s moving on. It gives me the freedom to move on myself.
Of course. Out of respect.
What? I’ve dated plenty of women. There was Joyce Kim, Leslie Winkle.
Uh, what about that girl last year at Comic-con?
Why not?
What happened to you?
Yes I have, it’s just a matter of actually making a date with someone.
Well, there’s Joyce Kim, but she defected back to North Korea so it’s a little geographically undesireable.
Look, I like Leslie, but she’s not interested in dating as much as using men as tools for stress release.
How?
Hey, Leslie.
Uh, sure.
Where did you hear that?
Like blue ice falling out of an airplane lavatory. Yep.
Are you suggesting another bout of stress release.
Really, what changed?
Yeah, I can see how that would… a bunch of people?
Oh, I’m flattered. So, how do you suggest we proceed?
Sounds fun.
Thank you, that’s very thoughtful.
Terrific.
I kind of have other plans tonight.
Well, the thing is, someone’s coming over.
Sheldon, it’s a date, I have a date coming over.
Why, what’s so unusual about me having a date?
Alright, alright. Well, uh, nevertheless, I have one now and I would appreciate it if you would, you know, make yourself scarce.
You know what I mean, could you just give us a little privacy?
Yes.
Yes.
I know it is, and if science ever discovers a second member of your species and you two would like some privacy I would be more than happy to get out of your way.
Yeah, it’s from Changs.
No, Changs.
It changed.
A little.
I sure hope so.
Okay, now my uncles are bald, but my Aunt Edna is one of the hairiest women you will ever meet. So… Sweet lady. It always tickles when she hugs me. (Sheldon knocks and enters again.) What now?
Listen, I’m sorry about all of Sheldon’s interruptions, he can be a bit of an eccentric.
Well, I think tonight was a very good start.
No problem, I’m very skilled at postponing intercourse. So I guess I’ll call you and we’ll arrange another evening.
Sure.
Hello.
Okay, well, goodnight. (Leans in to kiss Leslie.)
Right (goes back inside flat. Closes door.)
Hey, why don’t we all move over there so Leslie can join us.
Don’t make this hard for me.
You’re right, it is simple. (Sits with Leslie.)
If the word is pee-pee, just do it.
Thank you.
Okay, well, there is a lot of merit to both theories.
Sheldon, don’t make that noise, it’s disrespectful.
Sorry Leslie, I guess I prefer my space stringy not loopy.
Truth, what truth? We’re talking about untested hypotheses, uh, it’s no big deal.
I guess we let them wait until they’re old enough and let them choose their own theory.
Wait, where are you going?
What’s the bright side?
Oh yeah.
Yeah, that’s great, you guys want corn dogs?
What’s going on?
Great, you know there are groceries outside of your apartment?
I only bring it up because your ice-cream is melting and it’s starting to attract wildlife.
Want to catch me up?
Uh-huh. Seriously, six months?
Hey, check it out, it’s just corn starch and water.
Beats me. They were playing all last night too.
No, that’s Marcie. Peppermint Patty’s just athletic.
Why should I do something, you’re the one who introduced her to online gaming.
Why don’t you just tell her to leave you alone.
Well, what am I supposed to do?
You mean, up until now we’ve been experiencing the happy funtime Sheldon?
I’ll go talk to her.
Yeah, I see that. Shouldn’t you be at work?
It’s Thursday. Listen, Penny.
Okay, um, here’s the thing, um, sometimes people, good people, you know, they start playing these games and they find themselves through no fault of their own, you know, kind of, addicted.
Well, i-i-i-it’s just if a person doesn’t have a sense of achievement in their real life it’s easy to lose themselves in a virtual world where they get a false sense of accomplishment.
Penny, you’ve got cheetos in your hair.
Wow.
Penny’s been keeping him up at night.
She’s gotten really hooked on Age of Conan, she’s playing non-stop.
Sheldon, wake up.
That’s not what she’s doing, Leslie, she’s just trying to shore up her self esteem, it has nothing to do with sex.
Leslie, you are way off base here.
Excuse me, this whole idea is insane.
Sheldon…
Hello.
Hi Tom. Sheldon? Didn’t I explain to you about your little mistake in the cafeteria?
Chosen by science?
You got Penny to sign up for online dating?
This is bad.
Really, really bad.
They never do.
Let’s see, Raj was the Kung Palo Chicken.
Who was the Shrimp with Lobster Sauce?
Penny, you don’t have to do that.
Oh yeah, two zero zero eight NQ sub seventeen.
You’d do the dolphins.
Are you proud of yourself?
Well, we’re going to go apologise to Raj and invite him out to dinner.
Well, he came over last night with some pretty good news, and we weren’t very supportive.
Really, do tell.
Okay, let’s try it this way, what if the People magazine thing is the best Raj is ever going to achieve?
Come on.
Not really, it’s what you and I would call condescension.
And when we go in there, let’s show Raj that we’re happy for him.
Smile. (He does, exaggeratedly.)
We’re here to see Koothrappali, not kill Batman.
Close enough, come on. (Knocking and entering.) Hi Raj.
Celebrate your thirty under thirty thing. Right Sheldon? (He smiles.)
Dr Gablehauser.
Sheldon!
Sheldon.
You can stop smiling now.
No.
Not yet.
You just got him this afternoon.
A lackey?
Almost.
Well, uh, no I… the… no.
Now. (They all get up and leave. Raj looks around himself, then leans over to the next table.)
Hey.
You look very nice.
Good night.
Yeah.
Terrific.
Anythingforagreencard.com?
You’re joking.
Pass.
It’s not a date, and that’s racist.
Let’s just eat so I can get to bed. With any luck tonight will be the night my sleep apnoea kills me.
Yes.
Yes.
Yes.
Yes.
Yes.
You’re welcome.
Just sit down and eat.
Alright, it’s shredded, what do you want me to do?
Sorry.
He’s not going to have intercourse with Penny.
Do the shrimpers feature in your story?
He’s irony impaired, just move on.
A griffin?
And mythological.
You want to breed a new friend?
That may well be, but the fact is, it wouldn’t kill us to meet some new people.
If we do get a new friend, he should be a guy you can trust. A guy who has your back.
Yeah, let’s see, money, women, technology, okay we’re agreed, our new friend is going to be Iron Man.
Uh-huh.
I’m not going to work.
Sheldon, I was up all night using the new free-electron laser for my X-ray diffraction experiment.
No.
Didn’t I tell you I’d be working nights, and that you’d have to make other arrangements.
And?
Goodnight, Sheldon.

dialogue: He’s funny, too. He does this hysterical impersonation of Stephen Hawking having phone sex. What are you wearing? That’s not, he does it better. Anyway, he said he was gonna take me to the gym tomorrow, so I’m gonna go practice my situps.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: Ow! Ow!

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: Yeah, I guess.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: Thanks for letting me try out your motorcycle.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: I had no idea it was so heavy. The thing just fell right over on me, didn’t it?

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: Oh, yeah. It’s just a little motorcycle accident.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: I don’t know. It’s all such a blur.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: Yeah, lucky for the bike it landed on my leg.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: I’m not indoorsy. I just wear the appropriate sun block because I don’t take melanoma lightly.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: Yeah, we’re examining the radiation levels of photomultiplier tubes for a new dark matter detector.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: Since when?

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: Since when?

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: Uh, yeah. I guess.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: Yeah, if you like that type.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: No, just neighbours.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: Actually, science is my lady.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: See ya. ‘Bye, Penny. Have fun. (Bangs head on door. Sheldon opens it.)

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: What it is is a cacophonous assault of eucalyptus, bayberry, cinnamon and vanilla. It’s as if my head were trapped in the pyjamas of a sultan.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: Oh, hey, Dave. And Penny, what a surprise.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: Yeah, I know. I’ve been offering to show you around for a year and a half. You always said you had yoga.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: Maybe I heard you wrong. A lot of words sound like yoga.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: Yes, please shut up. So, um, Dave, don’t you think you and I should get back to the lab? You know, that dark matter isn’t going to detect itself.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: That’s funny. By the way, my leg is killing me. Thanks for asking.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: Yippee.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: Brilliant.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: Do whatever you want.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: My leg is killing me. Thanks for asking.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: Okay, I have just one question for you. While I am perfectly happy with the way things are between us, you said that you didn’t want to go out with me because I was too smart for you! Well, news flash, lady, David Underhill is ten times smarter than me! You’d have to drive a railroad spike into his brain for me to beat him at checkers! Next to him, I’m like one of those sign-language gorillas who knows how to ask for grapes! So, my question is, what’s up with that?

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: Sorry, I’m sorry, I’m sorry! Never mind, we’re cool.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: Really? Why would you say that?

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: He tried to take nude photos of you?

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: Oh, yeah. I’m so… oh, that’s terrible.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: Well, uh, the important thing is he’s married and that’s terrible!

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: Lactose.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: Smooth.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: Come on, it’s Christmas, just give me this one.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: By the way, my leg is killing me. Thanks for asking.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: Merry Christmas.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: Very good, thanks for asking. Come on in.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: Oh, a gift certificate for motorcycle lessons. Very thoughtful.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: Oh, then, I think you’ll appreciate what I got you.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: You know, ’cause you’re so into science.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 11 – The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
dialogue: It’s a Saturnalia miracle.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: Maybe we should start small.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: How about the toaster oven?

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: What did I ever do to Jimmy Mullins in the third grade? He still punched me in the face with my own fists. Sorry, you little nerd, you were just in the wrong boys’ room at the wrong time.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: That’ll do it.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: Uh-huh?

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: Killer robot. We built it.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: Howard, why don’t we just work on the robot?

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: I’m begging you, stop talking.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: Howard, where you going?

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: Wow.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: He said maybe we should enter you in the killer robot competition.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: I don’t know, now they’re just yelling about Popsicles. Sounds like Penny really got to him.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: Yes, we did, Kripke.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: Come on, is that really necessary?

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: No, don’t make it so. Barry, we can’t fight you tomorrow, our engineer is incapacitated.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: Hey, you got a minute?

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: I need you to apologize to How…

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: Come on. Wolowitz won’t come out of his house and we need him for a robot battle.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: The robot didn’t hurt his feelings.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: He’s been in bed for two days.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: He’s not with a… does it really matter who or what he’s with? The guy is devastated.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: Okay, don’t take this as a criticism, but you kind of have that overexposed-to-gamma-rays thing going on.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: You know, like, most of the time, you’re the easygoing Bruce Banner, but then, when you get angry, you kind of turn into, like, you know, grrrrr!

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: Seriously? Gamma rays? Bruce Banner? You didn’t get The Incredible Hulk from that? Never mind, just, please go talk to him.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: Well, maybe you can go at it from a different angle, like, um, you see a glimmer of goodness in him and you only said what you said because you want to nurture it and make it shine.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: Okay, let’s try it this way. Remember the day that we first met and you asked me to go to your boyfriend’s apartment to get your TV back and he was nine feet tall and he took my pants off and you said… what was that? What did you say? Oh, yes, you said you owed me one.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: I came home with no pants.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: Thank you. I should probably give you a heads up about his mother.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: She’s a delightful woman. You’ll love her.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: Oh, my God. That’s Kripke’s robot?

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: Sheldon, we have to call it off.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: Oh, please, we’ve spent our whole lives running away from fights. Personally, I can squeeze through a hole in a fence half my size.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: You want to prepare him? Install a bladder and a pair of shorts so he can wet himself.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: Not yet.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: Nice little bot you’ve got here.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: What’s this do, spin?

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: Neat. Good work. Sheldon, we’ve got to call this off.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: I just want to make sure that we’re all clear, standard robotic fighting league rules apply.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: Run, Monte, run!

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: Go, go, go, go!

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: Well, so much for making up for the emotional wounds of childhood.

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: Forget the robot. What happened to you?

episode_name: Series 02 Episode 12 – The Killer Robot Instability
dialogue: Penny.
Ah, no kidding! A Fu Man Chu? A handlebar pencil?
Alright this is cruel, we better let him finish before his head explodes.
Hey Kripke.
Alright, please don’t cheer me up anymore.
Good luck getting time on it. The only people he lets use it are his friends.
There you go. Now any e-mail from Wolowitz will go right into your spam folder.
Yeah, I got the same one. And that’s not a bathing suit, it’s a tan line.
Oh he’s trying to make a new friend.
Well, unless he’s makes one out of wood like Gepetto, I don’t think it’s gonna happen.
There was a flier on the bulletin board at the university. Roommate wanted. Whistlers need not apply.
I assumed he was joking. You’d be surprised how many particle physicists have a whimsical side.
I don’t know, how do carbon atoms form a benzene ring? Proximity and valence electrons.
I suppose. I do miss whistling though.
I answered every question Sheldon.
Aw, you picked up on that huh?
Come on! There’s over 200 questions. And look at some of these things. Sheldon is to camaraderie, as the space shuttle is to blank?
Hold on. I put some real work into that!
It’s kinda cute, until you get to the scrotum.
Sheldon, I’m not going to defend a big-balled raccoon.
What I’m trying to say is that, maybe you can’t approach this as a purely intellectual exercise.
Well, remember when you tried to learn how to swim using the internet?
On the floor.
Then why learn how to swim?
No! no, my point is, if you want to learn how to make friends, then just go out to a coffee shop or a museum. Meet people. Talk to them. Take an interest in their lives.
Where are we going?
Why don’t you just lie down on the floor and swim there?
Okay, if you’re gonna start sniffing people, I’m gonna go get a hot pretzel.
Sheldon, what are you doing?
No you’re not, let’s go.
Don’t look up, there’s cameras.
Sheldon, there is no algorithm for making friends!
Yes, he’s new at the zoo.
Uh-oh, he’s stuck in an infinite loop.
I’m sorry. Can we please just do it one more time?
It’s a little thing but you really do miss it.
How was rock climbing?
Want some Chinese food?
In the bathroom.
What’s that?
Can I whistle?
He had Lysine but changed it.
I didn’t think he had it in him.
Hmmm.
We’ve got to be missing something. Let’s start again. The movie is playing here at 7:20, here at 7:40, here at 8:10 and here at 8:45.
Why? They’re state-of-the-art digital projection, 20-channel surround sound.
Well, it’s gonna take at least an hour to eat, and I don’t see a Sheldon-approved restaurant proximate to a Sheldon-approved theatre.
Sheldon, would you be prepared, on a non-precedential basis, to create an emergency ad-hoc Slurpie-Icee equivalency?
Bye, Sheldon.
Interesting.
Do I have to?
Why?
Hey, Penny. How was work?
Stop it!
He’s not lying, he does find that fascinating.
Weird.
Did you guys have an argument?
Well, you clearly did something to aggravate her.
Here you go. Oh, you owe me another two dollars. The price of mu-shu pork went up.
Here you go, Penny. Shrimp with lobster sauce.
Don’t worry about it. It’s my treat.
It’s, whatever. Ten, eleven dollars.
Fourteen fifty, but it’s no biggie, you’ll get the next one. (Raj whispers something to Howard)
It was fourteen fifty, but it’s okay.
Oh, wait, you lent her money?
Where are you going?
But if you’re ever short, there’s always a couple of fifties in Green Lantern’s ass.
Hey.
A little mood lighting, huh?
Yeah, they’re very considerate that way.
Fourteen dollars, huh?

Back in the pocket it goes. Look, you do understand that Sheldon really doesn’t care when he gets the money back. It’s actually one of the few idiosyncrasies that doesn’t make you want to, you know, kill him.
So you’re a little behind on your bills. Everybody gets behind on their bills.
Well, what was the plan?
Was there a plan B?

It’s probably not as bad as you think. Let’s take a look. Maybe we can find some corners to cut. Oh, here’s something, if you don’t have electricity, then you probably don’t need cable. Just a suggestion. 170 dollars for acting classes?
You’ve had an acting job where you got paid?
Actually, it kind of… let’s keep looking. Whoa, what’s eighteen hundred dollars to the Los Angeles County Superior Court?
Nothing? It sounds like you got caught speeding going 4,000 miles an hour.
Your ex-boyfriend?
What?
I would hope so.
Did he pay you back?
And that’s based on the inherent credit-worthiness of people who get drunk and urinate on police vehicles?
Well what are you gonna do?
Oh, no. Oh, you don’t want to do that.

Well, moving is a big deal. You have to go to the supermarket and get boxes, and if they’re not clean, then your books smell like melons, and it’s just, like… Why don’t you just get a roommate and stay here?
Well, I’m sure the guy living with Sheldon wouldn’t mind moving in with you.
Really?
Hey, what’s going on?
Hey, you guys want to go on a real live quest?
– Come on. It’ll be fun.
Do you guys remember Penny’s ex-boyfriend Kurt? (They all hold their hands above their heads) Yeah, that’s him. It turns out he owes Penny a lot of money, and I’m gonna go get it from him.
Really? You’re just gonna let me go by myself?
I could use some help.
You guys are unbelievable, you play a game to simulate adventure, but when there’s real adventure out there in the real world, you just wimp out.
I do.
I’m not afraid of him.
Excuse me. When Frodo left the Shire to take the one ring to Mordor, didn’t Samwise, Pippin and Merry go with him?
Well?
Fine. Just enjoy your little game. I’ll make this quest on my own.
You guys suck. (Leaves. Comes back) Come on, please? He’s so big.
Okay, is everyone clear on the plan?
Guys, there are four of us and one of him.
Okay, how about this? I’ll do the talking, you just stand behind me and try to look formidable.
Hi, Kurt.
I don’t really go by Lenny, but that’s okay. Um, you remember Sheldon, Howard and Raj.
Sheldon, not now.
Okay, here it is. Penny’s in kind of a financial jam, and the money that you owe her would go a long way to solving her problems.
No, no, she’s too proud to ask for the money. I, on the other hand, feel you should honour your debt.
Feel is a kind of a… it’s a strong word. Um, I just think it would be a nice gesture on your part.
No, the problem isn’t solved. He just blew us off.
No. You can leave if you want to. I’m gonna see this through.
I guess, technically, that was my fault. (Knocks) I’m not leaving here without Penny’s money.
I don’t need backup. I have right on my side. And I’m wearing cargo shorts under my pants.
Hey.
Yeah. Hang on. Sheldon!
It’s kind of a fashionable look these days.
Hey, I know it’s none of my business, but where did the money come from?
Really? Did he say why?
That’s it? Did he give any reason as to why he came to this moral epiphany?
Bye.
Penny’s hooking up with her jerk of an ex-boyfriend and I have indelible ink on my forehead!
Great.
Can’t we just postpone it till the spring? Maybe next summer?
No, I didn’t realize it had been so long. Sure, I guess there’s no other choice but to just go ahead and do it.
Aren’t there any other options? There’s not a lot of room, it’s gonna be uncomfortable.
Okay, bye. My mother’s coming to visit.
Good to see you, Mother.
Here’s your tea, Mother.
Yes.
Yes.
Yes.
Yes.
Yes.
Yes.
Yes.
I’ll start again.
Here’s your tea, Mother. So, what are you guys talking about?
Swell. If you’re lucky, maybe she’ll show you the PowerPoint presentation.
So, Mother, what’s new?
All right. Uh, what’s new with you?
Maybe something less personal.
Oh, my God. What happened?
Yeah I, I thought you guys might hit it off.
I hate to tell you, but the only warm memories I have of my childhood are of my Uncle Floyd.
Sheldon, you don’t give your mother enough credit. She’s warm, she’s loving, she doesn’t glue electrodes to your head to measure your brain waves while potty training.
Please, don’t go there, Howard.
Boy, you suck.
Why are you doing this?
You know, rather than mock me, my friends might realize that this is difficult and try to help me through it.
That was fast.
Howard lives with his mother and Raj can’t speak to women unless he’s drunk. Go.
He lives in the same room where his bassinet was.
You brought your husband to work, you know the rules. Meesa thinking yousa looking pretty sad now too, betcha, betcha.
There’s no hurry, Mother, tell them more about their secret love for each other.
Fine. Let’s go. I think you’ll find my work pretty interesting. I’m attempting to replicate the dark matter signal found in sodium iodide crystals by the Italians.
No.
You got alcohol?
Yep.
Oh, relax. She took Sheldon to the hospital to get a brain scan.
Nothing. Mother likes looking at brains and Sheldon likes getting his brain scanned.
She’s only been here a day and a half and I’m seriously considering alcoholism as a new career path.
You can’t let her get into your head.
It’s too late for me. My head is her summer house.
Oh, yeah, there she is. Hi, Mom.
Did you get the part?
Hey, you want to talk about not getting love from a parent. You know what I used to do when I was little to have some sensation of human contact?
Of course she did. Anyway, that’s not what I was gonna say. When I was ten years old, I built a hugging machine.
Yeah. I got a dressmaker’s mannequin, I stuffed it with an electric blanket so it would be warm, and built two radio-controlled arms that would hug me and pat my back.
You know what the saddest part was?
My father used to borrow it.
Uh-huh.
I’m sorry, I didn’t hear anything after lick.
Right. Ah! Where’s the lime? (Penny has the lime in her mouth) Oh, okay, we’re sharing.
This is actually gonna happen.

You shush, I’m happy, I want to talk about it. You know what my mother would say about this? She would say because you were not loved by your father and I was not loved by my mother, that having sex is our way of making up for the intimacy we didn’t get as children.
I don’t know. Foreplay?
Ummm, I’m gonna go with “no.”
Come on, you’re trying to have sex with your father, and I’m okay with that.
She said shush. I should have shushed. (Enters apartment. Sheldon and Beverley are inside duetting on Journey’s “Any Way You Want It” on Rock Star.)
All right, Mother. Um, have a nice flight.
Morning.
You don’t have to. Ever.
Good-bye, Mother.
There’s no way we can get to the ridge. The Chemistry Department has us completely cut off.
I forget. Which one is Hammer of the Gods?
No, that shouldn’t be a problem, Venus is up during the day. They’re probably just all staring at the sky.
Yeah, more cutbacks.
You know what baffles me, Sheldon?
Hey, Leslie.
Yeah, okay, but what’s with the back-scratching and the meow!
Thank you.
Are you done?
What about it, Howard?
I don’t care about that.
You and Leslie?
And the rest of us have had our budgets cut to the bone.
Calm down. We’ll figure it out.
Here we go.
Don’t sit in his spot.
Okay, that should do it.
That’s a lot of shoes you ordered.
Yeah. You ought to come out with us sometime.
There’s a chance.
We? No, no, no, you had your chance to be we for, like, a year and a half now. Right now, you are you, and you are screwed.
Well, we’re not gonna tell him I did it.
Just to shoot the couch with a paintball gun?
We could tell him they wanted the couch to stay away from their boyfriend.
Mm, butt print. There’s no discernible butt print.
It’s too small and too perfect.
You’re welcome.
Sheldon! How was the comic book store?
Great, great. Did you walk the whole way? It’s a little chilly.
Isn’t that terrific? He is such a good friend. You know what the best thing about friends is?
No, no, friends forgive the little things.
Don’t you dare, missy.
What do you mean?
I don’t know what you’re talking about. Oh, that. Penny did that.
Why don’t you just eat in your desk chair?
Wackadoodle.
If it were your head, it would be.
Oh, for God’s sake, Sheldon.
No, it’s Leslie Winkle. It’s a long story.
I thought we were going to play Halo tonight.
That’s not fair. You’re not even a physicist.
Get out.
Why are you crouching there?
I don’t know. Texas?
Really? Great. Sheldon, look. Good as new.
Nothing, it’s what’s wrong with him.
Penny, Penny, I think I know what to do. Sheldon, I have some bad news.
I’m afraid so. You know the cashew chicken I get you Monday nights?
Szechuan Palace closed two years ago.
Golden Dragon.
Yeah, well, before they went out of business, I bought 4,000 containers. I keep them in the trunk of my car.
I thought that might take his mind off the cushion.
Oh, God, I wish I had.
Yeah, buddy?
Okay, first of all, Penny, thank you for coming.
Penny is an amazing shot. I think we have a real chance to win this week.

Okay. Now, we all run out. Sheldon and I will cut to the left behind these trees. Raj, Howard and Leslie flank to the right behind the rocks. Then we’ll all have a great view as Penny runs out and kills everyone else in sight.
What is it, Sheldon? (Sheldon shoots Penny)
Sheldon, Penny was our only hope.
He’s right. You can’t. (Shoots Sheldon)
Where are you going?
Okay, then we won’t touch the hard drive. We’ll just erase the first season of Battlestar.
It’s perfect.
It’s just for my notebooks. Thanks, Penny.
This conference is kind of a big thing. The keynote address is being delivered by George Smoot.
You’ve heard of him?
Yeah, I wish.
Well, we had a vote. Three of us voted for airplane, Sheldon voted for train, so we’re taking the train.
Hey, we’re all going over to the Apple store to make fun of the guys at the Genius Bar. You want to come?
What are you doing?
Well, that does sound much simpler. How long is this going to take?
Wow. Teasing the guys at the Apple store seems a little redundant now.
I wouldn’t expect you to. I’ll see you later.
Why not?
Sheldon, we’ve been on this train 90 seconds, and you’ve already said a thousand words. Just tell us where to sit and shut up.
Yeah, maybe. Meanwhile back in the 21st century, people are raising their tray tables and putting their seat-backs in an upright position ’cause it’s time to land in San Francisco.
Oh, look, now he’s boring on an international scale.
Is that who I think it is?
Maybe John Connor’s aboard and she’s protecting him from an evil Terminator.
Thank you.
At least he’s off the train crap.
My money’s on tuck and roll.
Excuse me, but what about me? Why don’t I get a shot?
You know, I’ve already got a gorgeous blonde back home at I can’t score with. I think I’ll let you two take this one.
So aren’t you going to go talk to her?
She’s probably heard every possible line, Howard. Why don’t you just try hello?
You’re going to need more than 11 hours.
What’s the matter?
So?
Okay, Sheldon, I’m going to say why and your answer cannot be because I forgot my flash drive.
Why do you have to give your paper to George Smoot?
So you’ll send him an e-mail when we get back.
Right. Of course.
Well, there’s nothing you can do about it, so relax, sit back, enjoy the clickety-clack of the steel wheels on the polished rails.
