He wasn’t in a car, but okay.
I honestly don’t.
If you want to drive, just drive. I don’t see why this has to be so complicated.
That’s not it because you’re clearly upset.
Why would I be upset?
Well, I just don’t think you’re gonna have a good time.
Why would you say you wanted to go if you didn’t?
O-o-o-okay, hold on, so if you don’t want to go and I don’t need to bring you, is everything good?
All right, problem solved.
Now you can come with us.
You know what? I’ve gone 12 times. Maybe I’ll sit out this year, too.
Yeah. Maybe you and I can do something fun that weekend.
Oh, how about we compromise and go on the Small World ride at Disneyland?

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 18 – The Escape Hatch Identification
dialogue: Aw, man, did you see this post from Raj?

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 18 – The Escape Hatch Identification
dialogue: No. He can’t afford his apartment, and he’s asking if anyone knows of a cheap place to live. I want to say India, but it seems mean.

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 18 – The Escape Hatch Identification
dialogue: We do have Sheldon’s old room. If he really needs a place to stay, I guess we should offer it to him.

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 18 – The Escape Hatch Identification
dialogue: Am I still a good friend if I wait and hope that Howard offers him a place to live first?

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 18 – The Escape Hatch Identification
dialogue: Hey, buddy, you still looking for a place to live?

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 18 – The Escape Hatch Identification
dialogue: You know, we have the extra bedroom, and if you need it, it’s yours.

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 18 – The Escape Hatch Identification
dialogue: It’s the least we can do.

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 18 – The Escape Hatch Identification
dialogue: I don’t have a loofah.

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 18 – The Escape Hatch Identification
dialogue: Hey.

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 18 – The Escape Hatch Identification
dialogue: Yeah, for a little while.

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 18 – The Escape Hatch Identification
dialogue: And I think it’s nice that you’re taking whatever medication Amy’s clearly giving you.

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 18 – The Escape Hatch Identification
dialogue: Just when I thought you couldn’t get any hotter.

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 18 – The Escape Hatch Identification
dialogue: Do not adjust the dosage. You nailed it.

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 18 – The Escape Hatch Identification
dialogue: I don’t know. Yours looks like he has worms.

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 18 – The Escape Hatch Identification
dialogue: Hey.

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 18 – The Escape Hatch Identification
dialogue: Perfect timing. Food’s ready.

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 18 – The Escape Hatch Identification
dialogue: You didn’t do anything, it’s Sheldon. That’d make a nice needlepoint pillow.

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 18 – The Escape Hatch Identification
dialogue: I don’t know who you talked to, but that wasn’t my mother.

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 18 – The Escape Hatch Identification
dialogue: Why are you saying we have marital problems? We don’t have marital problems.

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 18 – The Escape Hatch Identification
dialogue: Look, just because we took our friend in does not mean that Penny and I are afraid to be alone.

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 18 – The Escape Hatch Identification
dialogue: Well, now that you point it out…

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 18 – The Escape Hatch Identification
dialogue: We do seem to keep finding room mates.

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 18 – The Escape Hatch Identification
dialogue: Did you know Raj moved out last night?

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 18 – The Escape Hatch Identification
dialogue: Leonard and Penny, I’m sorry for all the trouble I’ve caused. I went to stay at Howard’s. PS Cinnamon’s with me, but if you feel like messing with Sheldon, tell him she’s loose in the building.

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 18 – The Escape Hatch Identification
dialogue: Should we go bring him back?

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 18 – The Escape Hatch Identification
dialogue: Oh, that was just because my mother got in my head. It’s like being possessed, but instead of Satan it’s, actually, it’s the same thing.

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 18 – The Escape Hatch Identification
dialogue: Well, great.

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 18 – The Escape Hatch Identification
dialogue: Just one second. Help, Cinnamon’s loose in the building.

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 18 – The Escape Hatch Identification
dialogue: You are not a burden, and we want you to come back and stay with us.
I thought we were getting breakfast before work.
It’s cute that you think that. Don’t worry about it.
Sure. You’re living here for free, I guess I owe you.
Bye.
Well, she’s done.
He does raise an interesting point.
I understand it, Sheldon.
Who’s Paul?
Oh, sure. Wait, Nancy?
Jerry?
Tina?
I went to your office Christmas party?
I’d still like to know who Jerry is.
That would be great. Thank you.
Or we could do something we’ll all enjoy, like play a board game.
I mean, they didn’t say anything, but I just kind of felt like I was being a weird third wheel.
Anyway, I figured I can hang out with my friends and have fun, too.
Oh, it’s just nice to be with people who are happy to have me around. Isn’t that right, Halley?
I mean, I’m glad they’re getting along, but it’s starting to make me uncomfortable.
A little, until I saw them in matching tops.
Well, what am I supposed to say, stop having fun without me?
I know, but he was my friend first. It’s like she’s stealing him and they’re just having the best time doing all their dumb girly stuff together.
You know, it’s nice to spend time with people who don’t talk about work like it’s some kind of soap opera.
Yeah.
I’m sure I’m overreacting.
I don’t want to sound like a jealous baby.
Anyway, I know it’s silly, but since Raj moved in, I’ve been feeling a little left out.
Thank you. I just feel…
Well, to be truthful…
Thank you. I…
Hey, Olsen twins…
Well, I mean, I’m sitting right here. You’re talking about my feelings and somehow leaving me out of the conversation.
I don’t know, you pretty much covered it.
Oh, I would, but we need to make a push on the air force project.
Yeah, why?
We’ve had this planned for a week.
I’m sorry, what is this plan you have?
When does that start?
It’s getting harder to pretend.
It can’t be four revolutions, it’s got to be seven.
Oh, my God, it’s seven.
Seven.
I got to admit, we didn’t think you’d be able to do two things at once.
I don’t know, we came home from work and we found you.
You did seem a little loopy when you showed up at the lab.
She’s kidding.
How could you lose that?
Well, it’s not across the hall.
But, boy, it is funny to think about.
Relax. I know when you go for a run, you stop for a donut.
Ask him.
You understood the math?
That’s just great.
I honestly don’t remember.
So Howard back Monday?
Hey. Want to join us?
So, Sheldon says you have a new girlfriend.
Hey, we’re all having dinner tonight. Why don’t the two of you join us?
Don’t you have any friends he can date?
Hey.
Is that it?
No, it’s always him.
So, Rebecca, how did you become a personal trainer?
Nice try. I’m not going.
Mm, just down there.
And we lived happily ever after.
O-o-o-o-oh.
That’s actually funny.
Oh, hello. Join us.
Wow, that’s a big step.
Is that Bert?
If you’re that upset, go get her back.
You called on him.
You don’t have to go. You’re welcome to hang with us.
It’s totally different. Bert’s money might run out, but I can beg until the end of time.
We’re pinned down.
Sheldon, why are you jumping up and down?
Aw.
Doing it right now. Oh, they can’t. There’s an important Little League game tomorrow.
Mm, if it makes you feel better, you still dress like a child.
Hot dogs.
You’re gonna have to be more specific.
More.
Oh, the video game. Yeah, that was bad.
How is super-aging any different than, like, doing crossword puzzles?
I drive you to work every day, my brain must look like the Hulk.
Yeah, I guess.
Honestly? It’s a little strange having dinner with your ex-boyfriend, and it’s not like we have a lot to talk about.
It’ll be fine, let’s just go.
Aaargh.
Ha, I knew you weren’t asleep.
I have Sheldon, that keeps most people away.
Oh, I know what he’s saying, and he’s not, he’s not funny.
She’s doing amazing. She can actually make a side effect, like 10% chance of liver failure, sound like a 90% chance of liver success.
Yeah. Although, when he was trying to figure out the tip, I’m pretty sure I saw smoke coming out of his ears. You’re not really considering working for him, are you?
Don’t you think it might be a little weird to work for someone you used to date?
Yeah, it’s weird.
No, no, I’m not jealous, I just think you have got a good thing going where you are right now, and you make great money and you haven’t slept with any of your co-workers.
Uh.
Of course I don’t want you to be unhappy, but I also want you to be smart, and working for an ex-boyfriend isn’t very smart. You don’t have to stop, just slow down, I’ll jump out.
No, I told her she was being not smart. Which was dumb.
We covered this, I’m dumb.
So you think it’s fine if she works for Zack?
Yeah, but she also used to sleep with Zack.
Thank you.
So you think it’s okay?
Hi.
That doesn’t seem to be where I shine. How about I just give you one of these?
Yeah, sorry.
Well, thanks. And I don’t want you to be stuck at a job you don’t like.
Well, I don’t love it, but if you really want to take this job, I’ll find a way to deal with it.
No, no, no, no, you’re, you’re unhappy there and then you’re gonna blame me for making you stay, and it’s fine, I’ll just, I’ll suck it up.
Yeah, see, now I feel terrible, like I’m being selfish and holding you back. What? Say something. Yeah, that is pretty annoying.
Absolutely. I just want you to be happy. And maybe a little turned on about how selfless I’m being.
Not if I want to be doing this later.
Thank you.
Hey, a toast. Thank you all for your support while we worked on our Air Force project. And please know that we could not have done it without you, so cheers.
First thing tomorrow morning, we’re back at it.
Hmm. I don’t care if this thing is burning out my retinas, it makes me feel special. Now, before we field test, I think we…
Where is everything?
It’s a secure lab in a classified facility, only the U.S. government and us.
Sir, I, I, I’m sorry but I just don’t get it. You came into our lab in the middle of the night and took our prototype and all of our research and didn’t even tell us?
Are you implementing phase two?
I can’t believe the Air Force would treat us like that.
Third floor, wrong apartment.
She might disappear, but she’s definitely not cleaning anything.
You won’t believe it, the military confiscated our project.
Yeah, what’s going on with you guys?
Oh, no. When?
So, are you excited to have your own place again?
Ah, we’ll miss you, too.
I’m trying. This is the best I can do. What are you doing?
Uh, could I talk to you in the hall for a sec?
Sheldon, you’re being silly.
Do you really care about that last one?
Instead of dwelling on the negative, think about this. Your girlfriend was given an amazing opportunity, which gives you an opportunity to show her that you’re a loving and supportive boyfriend.
All right, let me start again. Uh, you and Amy…
Thank you.
Should we give them their privacy?

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 24 – The Long Distance Dissonance
dialogue: Well, the last three nights I’ve had to take him to get a haircut, to the train store, and to a Walgreens in Arcadia where they still have the good ibuprofen. Now ask me how I’m doing with Amy gone.

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 24 – The Long Distance Dissonance
dialogue: Shut up.

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 24 – The Long Distance Dissonance
dialogue: Oh, that would be great.

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 24 – The Long Distance Dissonance
dialogue: Great. Tonight he wants to look at ladders at Home Depot.

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 24 – The Long Distance Dissonance
dialogue: He doesn’t; he just likes looking at them. Bring a book.

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 24 – The Long Distance Dissonance
dialogue: Hello.

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 24 – The Long Distance Dissonance
dialogue: Oh. I love those.

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 24 – The Long Distance Dissonance
dialogue: Wait, isn’t she the grad student that used to follow him around?

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 24 – The Long Distance Dissonance
dialogue: Knowing Sheldon, nothing.

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 24 – The Long Distance Dissonance
dialogue: He just made her laugh, something’s wrong.

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 24 – The Long Distance Dissonance
dialogue: Ah, did you see that? She just touched his hand and he didn’t swat it away. What is happening?

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 24 – The Long Distance Dissonance
dialogue: Penny laid into me, too. Apparently, I’m overly fixated on premium Swiss chocolate bars.

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 24 – The Long Distance Dissonance
dialogue: If I take a Lactaid a half-hour before and some Pepto right after.

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 24 – The Long Distance Dissonance
dialogue: Eh, I’m worth it.

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 24 – The Long Distance Dissonance
dialogue: Like what?

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 24 – The Long Distance Dissonance
dialogue: No offence, Stuart, but the woman’s a doctor.

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 24 – The Long Distance Dissonance
dialogue: You kept walking. I think you did.

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 24 – The Long Distance Dissonance
dialogue: Yeah, she’s definitely going after Sheldon.

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 24 – The Long Distance Dissonance
dialogue: And you actually got in a pool?

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 24 – The Long Distance Dissonance
dialogue: Uh, so, Ramona, tell us about yourself. Do you, do you have a boyfriend?

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 24 – The Long Distance Dissonance
dialogue: You think you should call Amy?

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 24 – The Long Distance Dissonance
dialogue: You got feet and legs, you do it.

episode_name: Series 10 Episode 24 – The Long Distance Dissonance
dialogue: Our pleasure.
